<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76794" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-745x497.jpg" alt="Electric motorcycle conversion for BMW boxers" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
<span class="lede">Dropping an electric</span> drivetrain into a classic motorcycle is hardly a new concept, but it&#8217;s still an endeavor largely reserved for outliers. The automotive electric &#8216;crate&#8217; motor industry is huge—but in the bike world, options are few and far between, and most <a href="https://www.bikeexif.com/category/electric-motorcycles" target="_blank" rel="noopener">electric motorcycle</a> conversions are one-offs.</p>
<p>That&#8217;s slowly changing though. A while back, Luuc Muis developed a <a href="https://www.bikeexif.com/electric-motorcycle-conversion-kit" target="_blank" rel="noopener">drop-in electric motor</a> for classic BMW boxers. Now the Parisian custom shop Mototherapy has launched its own electric motorcycle conversion, also targeting the beloved boxer.<span id="more-76775"></span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76783" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-745x497.jpg" alt="Electric motorcycle conversion for BMW boxers" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-7.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
Mototherapy is calling the project &#8216;Ride Mercury,&#8217; and this is their prototype, the &#8216;R01.&#8217; It uses a classic <a href="https://www.bikeexif.com/tag/bmw-r75" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BMW R75</a> as a foundation, with most of the original bike left stock (albeit carefully restored).</p>
<p>&#8220;Our primary goal is to breathe new life into motorcycles with character,” says company founder Jean-Marie Raymon. “This focus has led us to place functionality at the center of our considerations. We&#8217;re not interested in creating a showroom curiosity; we aim for a conscious and useful enhancement.”</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76787" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-745x497.jpg" alt="Electric motorcycle conversion for BMW boxers" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-11.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
Taking advantage of the BMW R75&#8217;s versatility, the Ride Mercury team has designed a full drivetrain that simply tucks into the chassis where the OEM engine, transmission, and airbox usually sit. It&#8217;s pretty much a plug-and-play system, with no frame mods required to make it work.</p>
<p>The motor itself peaks at 20 kW, sending up to 340 Nm of torque and 30 hp to the back wheel. The current maximum range is 150 km [93 miles], with a six-hour charge time via the onboard 1.8 kW charger. (Plans for a fast charging solution are currently in the works.)</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76780" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-745x497.jpg" alt="Electric motorcycle conversion for BMW boxers" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-4.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
All of the requisite parts are packaged into bespoke aluminum housings, with steel used for structural components. Two of the bike&#8217;s four batteries are housed in finned casings that mimic the boxer&#8217;s iconic cylinder heads; another two sit further forward. The motor is housed where the transmission used to be, and is connected directly to the BMW&#8217;s original driveshaft.</p>
<p>Because everything has been designed in-house, the layout is constantly evolving. Ride Mercury already has a second-gen design that places the &#8216;cylinder heads&#8217; a little lower and includes more ventilation. Various options for the front engine cover are in the works too.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76781" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-745x497.jpg" alt="Electric motorcycle conversion for BMW boxers" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-5.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
The R01 is just a proof of concept—which is why it uses Ride Mercury&#8217;s prototype &#8216;engine block&#8217; design, and why much of the rest of the bike is still original. The goal is to show that an electric drivetrain can be retrofitted to a vintage motorcycle without having to reimagine the whole machine.</p>
<p>The only parts that have been upgraded, apart from the obvious, are the headlight&#8217;s internals and the digital dashboard that links to the motor&#8217;s controller. Right now, the OEM fuel tank is just an empty shell—but the crew is working on converting it into a storage space, or a place to package an upgraded charging port.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76784" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-745x497.jpg" alt="Electric motorcycle conversion for BMW boxers" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-8.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
The whole package won&#8217;t be available as a &#8216;crate&#8217; system quite yet (although the possibility of selling a DIY kit later on hasn&#8217;t been ruled out). Instead, Ride Mercury will build you a complete electric BMW R75 for the tidy starting price of €29,500 [around $31,233]. Pre-orders for the R01 open next week, with the first machines expected to ship in the second quarter of next year.</p>
<p>Each build includes a full refurb of the donor bike, plus various custom options. &#8220;With all the care we&#8217;ve put into the design and development of our module, it was unthinkable that machines bearing the Ride Mercury name wouldn&#8217;t receive a full makeover,” says the company&#8217;s other co-founder, Cédric De Azevedo. “Our approach to retrofitting goes far beyond a simple engine conversion.&#8221;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-76790" src="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-745x497.jpg" alt="Electric motorcycle conversion for BMW boxers" width="745" height="497" srcset="https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/bmw-electric-motorcycle-conversion-13.jpg 1490w" sizes="(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px" /><br />
But does it make sense to yank a BMW R75&#8217;s motor out to electrify it? If that motor is blown (which is admittedly rare for old airheads), then why not?</p>
<p>According to Ride Mercury&#8217;s stats, retrofitting a bike or car with an electric powertrain is up to 50% more environmentally friendly than manufacturing a brand new electric vehicle. If you have to go green, this sure is a classy way to do it.</p>
